=== Parliamentary QA ===
Title: Reports of Abandoned Vapes in Transport Areas and Extension of Vape Disposal Bins
Date: 2025-10-14
Source: Singapore Parliament
Document Type: Parliamentary QA (Written Answer)
Topic: Vaping, Disposal Bins, Transport Areas, Enforcement, HSA

Summary:
- Question about increase in abandoned vapes in transport areas, extending vape disposal bins to non-restricted areas, and developing SOPs with Public Transport Operators.
- Ministry of Health / HSA response:
  - Reports of abandoned e-vaporisers in transport areas have not increased.
  - Vape disposal bins are located at QuitVape and rehabilitation programme sites; individuals encouraged to discard vapes there or in locations not easily accessible to others.
  - About 1,000 frontline Public Transport Operator staff trained by HSA for enforcement in a safe and consistent manner.

Key Entities:
- Ministry of Health (MOH)
- Health Sciences Authority (HSA)
- Public Transport Operators (~1,000 trained staff)
- Ms Yeo Wan Ling, MP (Punggol GRC)

Key Concepts:
- Enforcement of vape regulations in public transport areas
- Placement of vape disposal bins at programme locations
- Training of frontline transport staff for safe enforcement
- Standard Operating Procedures for confronting vape users

Body:
1. No observed increase in abandoned e-vaporisers in transport areas.
2. E-vaporiser disposal bins available at programme locations; safe discarding encouraged.
3. 1,000 transport staff trained by HSA for enforcement duties.

Author / Issuer:
Ministry of Health (MOH), Health Sciences Authority (HSA)
Date of Issue: 2025-10-14
